# TSX Components

In addition to V components, Velt supports writing components in TSX (TypeScript + JSX).

## Why TSX?

- **TypeScript Type Safety** - Prop type checking
- **Leverage Existing Skills** - Use React/TypeScript knowledge
- **Ecosystem** - npm package integration

## Writing TSX Components

### Basic Structure

```tsx
// components/Hero.tsx
interface HeroProps {
  title: string;
  subtitle?: string;
  btnText?: string;
  btnLink?: string;
}

export default function Hero({ 
  title, 
  subtitle, 
  btnText, 
  btnLink 
}: HeroProps) {
  return (
    <section className="hero">
      <h1 className="hero-title">{title}</h1>
      {subtitle && <p className="hero-subtitle">{subtitle}</p>}
      {btnText && btnLink && (
        <a href={btnLink} className="btn btn-primary">
          {btnText}
        </a>
      )}
    </section>
  );
}
```

### Using in VDX

```markdown
+++
layout = "landing"
title = "My Site"
+++

<Hero
  title="Welcome"
  subtitle="This is my site"
  btnText="Get Started"
  btnLink="./docs.html"
/>
```

